value.title: Biden to hit the campaign trail after negative test for COVID-19
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden plans to head to the battleground state of Michigan and resume campaigning on Friday after testing negative for coronavirus, hours after President Donald Trump was sidelined by contracting the virus.

value.title: Trump’s campaign ‘may be more focused and disciplined’ without in-person events: Karl Rove

value.title: 'This was avoidable': Trump has been downplaying the virus from the start

value.title: Pelosi: Trump diagnosis 'tragic,' hopefully leads to 'saner approach' to pandemic
value.excerpt: Speaker Nancy Pelosi said that President Trump’s COVID-19 diagnosis is “tragic” and “very sad,” but predictable, given his frequent contact with crowds.
